    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Kerry vs. Bush, Toe to Toe</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jonathan L Gleit letter on Mar 10 article cites examples of Pres Bush's own flip-flopping on issues</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So the Bush administration wants to paint John Kerry as a ''flip-flopper'' (''Bush Team Tries to Capture Critical First Judgments,'' Political Memo, March 10).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>So the Bush administration wants to paint John Kerry as a ''flip-flopper'' (''Bush Team Tries to Capture Critical First Judgments,'' Political Memo, March 10).</p>
        <p>Perhaps the administration protests too much.</p>
        <p>I seem to recall an agenda that promoted reduced carbon dioxide emissions, then eschewed them; despised deficits, then oversaw the largest ever; guffawed at nation-building, then embraced it.</p>
        <p>And that was from just one former governor of Texas.</p>
        <p>JONATHAN L. GLEIT  Tarrytown, N.Y., March 11, 2004</p>
      </block>
